The paper deals with improving the performance of automated machine learning methods using natural language processing techniques. Specifically, it uses language embeddings to augment recommendations of datasets and algorithms, and uses a neural architecture to learn the distance between best-performing pipelines. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
